From 0e7c4fe2cd1e360b7a64615d8765c386ba66abf9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ihar Hrachyshka <ihar.hrachyshka@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 19:54:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] tests: use kill -0 for alttab liveness check

The run-in-xvfb test only needs to verify that the alttab
process started by the script is still alive. ps -p is
a poor fit for that: on Darwin it can fail with
"Operation not permitted" even when the process is
running.

Use kill -0 instead. It is enough for this same-user
liveness probe and allows the test suite to run on
Darwin.
---
 test/run-in-xvfb.test | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/test/run-in-xvfb.test b/test/run-in-xvfb.test
index 7c33ac3..24cf76f 100755
--- a/test/run-in-xvfb.test
+++ b/test/run-in-xvfb.test
@@ -122,7 +122,7 @@ check_alttab()
 {
     stage="$1" ; comment="$2"
     sleep 0.5
-    if ! ps -p "$alttab" >/dev/null ; then
+    if ! kill -0 "$alttab" >/dev/null 2>&1 ; then
         echo "not ok $stage - $comment"
         exit 1
     else
-- 
2.50.1
